//Assuming that youâ€™re asking it from a competitive programming point of view.
//Use long long int whenever the input constraints exceed  1x10^5.
EG:
Constraints:
2 <= N <= 10^5
1 <= Q <= 10^5
0 <= A[i] <= 10^9 
0 <= K < N
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
To avoid overflow or segmentation fault, use long long: 
long long n, q;
long long k;
